summary:
My career in education started in the childhood bedroom of my small Polish apartment when I excitedly subjected my two younger brothers to hours and hours of English language lessons.

Since then, I have enjoyed many positions in education: teaching ESL to high school and adult learners, a stint in corporate training & development in Warsaw, and teaching college writing & literature in Europe and in the U.S. until I transitioned to educational development in higher education, first at the CTLs in the U.S. and now in the Netherlands.

As an educational developer, for nearly nine years I have been helping higher education institutions function effectively as teaching and learning communities. I have done that by: 
🔹designing and facilitating pedagogy training programs--such as learning communities, communities of practice, course design institutes, and fellowships--for early-, mid-, and late-career faculty; 
🔹advising academic experts on educational innovation, active learning, learning design, assessment, and classroom community building, among other topics;
🔹mentoring graduate students for careers in higher education;
🔹translating learning science into practical resources and applied learning-centered classroom interventions;
🔹supporting integration of learning technologies.

Currently, as an education coach at the Eindhoven University of Technology, my job is to support the university's education innovation strategy by helping teachers develop skills in formative assessment, assessment as learning, and Challenge-Based Learning.

🌷 𝑴𝒚 𝒗𝒂𝒍𝒖𝒆𝒔: Love of learning 🔹 Sustainability 🔹 Kindness 🔹 Inclusion 🔹 Authenticity 🔹 Practicing “what if”

